1 HOUSE BILL NO. 521
2 INTRODUCED BY C. SCHOMER, V. RICCI, M. VINTON, G. LAMMERS, S. VINTON, M. YAKAWICH, J.
3 SCHILLINGER, G. OBLANDER, D. LENZ, B. MITCHELL, K. SEEKINS-CROWE
4
5 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT PROVIDING THAT A PERSON CONVICTED OF A CRIME WHO
6 IS INJURED DURING THE COMMISSION OF THE CRIME HAS NO RIGHT OF ACTION.”
7
8 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
9
10 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Person convicted of crime -- no right of action for injuries and
11 damages. A person who is convicted of a crime and is injured or suffers other damages during the commission
12 of the crime does not have a right of action to recover damages if a victim causing the injury or damages did not
13 use any force or used justifiable force, as defined in Title 45, chapter 3, part 1.
14
15 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Codification instruction. [Section 1] is intended to be codified as an
16 integral part of Title 27, chapter 1, part 5, and the provisions of Title 27, chapter 1, part 5, apply to [section 1].
17 - END -
